name: Highfield Park Community Orchard
description: Two large orchards (Hixberry and Cell Barnes) featuring hundreds of apple and pear trees open for community picking.

name: Incredible Edible St Albans - Civic Centre
short_description: Urban veg in the city heart.
description: Public planters outside the council offices and library featuring chard, kale, and aromatic herbs.

name: Heartwood Forest Hazelnuts
description: The newer plantings and existing ancient pockets contain a vast amount of hazel and dogwood.

name: Verulamium Park Wild Garlic
short_description: Spring ramsons by the River Ver.
description: The wooded banks of the River Ver, particularly near the Causeway, are thick with wild garlic in spring.

name: The Alban Way Blackberries
description: This disused railway path is a continuous corridor of blackberries and elder bushes from St Albans to Hatfield.

name: Bernards Heath Sweet Chestnuts
description: Mature sweet chestnut trees line the edges of the woods overlooking the historic heath.

name: Gorhambury Estate Sloes
description: The public footpaths through the estate are lined with blackthorn bushes (sloes) and hawthorn.

name: Batchwood Walnuts
description: Mature walnut trees can be found in the wooded borders of the golf course and public paths.

name: Clarence Park Rosehips
description: The perimeter shrubbery of the park contains many wild rose species for autumn hip gathering.

name: Sopwell Nunnery Wild Herbs
description: Feral herbs and wild mint often grow in the damp ground near the ruins and the river.

name: Sandridge Village Orchard
description: A small stand of mixed fruit trees planted by the local community for shared use.

name: Jersey Farm Woodland Elder
description: Abundant elder bushes for flowers and berries grow along the green lanes and woodland edges.

name: Ver Valley Meadow Sorrel
description: Find wild sorrel and watermint in the damp meadows heading south toward Park Street.

name: Fleetville Incredible Edible Planters
description: Planters featuring strawberries, chives, and mint near the community centre.

name: Redbourn Road Wild Plums
description: Several wild plum and bullace trees can be found on the wide verges of the old road toward Redbourn.
